{
  "texts": [
    "The evolution of artificial intelligence in legal practice: innovations, challenges, and ethical implicationsThere are two major phases to the evolution of AI in the legal sphere.",
    "The first stage might be thought of as a moderateinnovative stage in which old legal practices are still prevalent but are enhanced by software and technical instruments.",
    "These legal technology tools help courts and solicitors handle cases more effectively [52].",
    "The second stage represents a significant advancement in legal automation and process optimisation technology.",
    "This stage includes integrating machine learning, natural language processing, and automated document evaluation."
  ]
}